.\" vigil.toml(5) — configuration file format
.\" Hand-authored roff (this file is included verbatim by `vigil man vigil.toml`).
.\" Sources of truth: src/config/, config/vigil.toml.
.TH VIGIL.TOML 5 "" "vigil" "File Formats Manual"
.SH NAME
vigil.toml \- configuration file for vigil(1) and vigild(8)
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B /etc/vigil/vigil.toml
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B vigil.toml
is the TOML configuration file consumed by
.BR vigil (1)
and
.BR vigild (8).
The daemon reads this file at startup; the CLI reads it for every command
that touches the baseline, audit log, or alert pipeline.

The path may be overridden by the
.B \-\-config
flag on
.BR vigil (1)
or by setting the
.B VIGIL_CONFIG
environment variable for
.BR vigild (8).
The full annotated example installed at
.I /usr/share/doc/vigil-baseline/vigil.toml.example
is the canonical reference. This page documents the table layout and the
fields most likely to require operator attention; it is intentionally not
exhaustive.
.SH FORMAT
The file is parsed as TOML 1.0. Unknown keys are rejected by default;
new fields added by a vigil upgrade are documented in the package
.B CHANGELOG.
Paths beginning with
.B ~
inside
.B [watch.*]
tables are expanded relative to the home directory of the user running
.BR vigil (1)
or to
.B HOME
for
.BR vigild (8).
.SH TABLES
.SS [daemon]
Runtime parameters for
.BR vigild (8).
.TP
.B pid_file
PID file written by
.BR vigild (8).
Default:
.IR /run/vigil/vigild.pid .
.TP
.B db_path
SQLite database holding the baseline, audit log, and ack ledger.
Default:
.IR /var/lib/vigil/baseline.db .
.TP
.B log_level
.B trace ", " debug ", " info ", " warn ", " error
\(em the structured log verbosity for tracing\-subscriber. May be
overridden at startup by
.BR RUST_LOG .
.TP
.B monitor_backend
.B fanotify " or " inotify .
.B fanotify
is the default and is required for the page\-cache disambiguation
features described under
.BR [detection] .
.TP
.B control_socket
Unix\-domain socket the daemon binds for the CLI. Mode 0660,
group\-readable by the
.B vigil
group created by the package.
.SS [scanner]
Periodic full\-tree rescan settings. The scanner is independent of the
inotify/fanotify event stream; it provides a defence in depth against
events lost to overflow or backend failure.
.TP
.B schedule
Cron expression for the scheduled scan. Default:
.B "0 3 * * *"
(03:00 daily).
.TP
.B mode
.B incremental " (default) or " full .
.TP
.B hash_algorithm
.B blake3 " (default) or " sha256 .
Changing this invalidates the existing baseline.
.TP
.B max_file_size
Bytes. Files larger than this are recorded but their content is not
hashed. Default: 2 GiB.
.SS [alerts]
Channels used to surface findings. Each finding is dispatched to every
enabled channel that passes the severity filter.
.TP
.B desktop_notifications
Send a D\-Bus desktop notification when a graphical session is active.
.TP
.B syslog
Forward findings to the system journal via libsystemd.
.TP
.B log_file
Append findings as one JSON object per line.
.TP
.B webhook_url
HTTPS endpoint to POST a finding payload to. Empty string disables.
.TP
.B rate_limit ", " cooldown_seconds
Token\-bucket throttling for each channel: at most
.I rate_limit
findings per
.I cooldown_seconds
window. Excess findings are coalesced into a single summary alert and
recorded in the audit log.
.SS [alerts.severity_filter]
Minimum severity per channel:
.B dbus_min_severity
and
.B log_min_severity .
Allowed values:
.B info ", " low ", " medium ", " high ", " critical .
.SS [exclusions]
.TP
.B patterns
Glob patterns matched against the file basename. Matches are excluded
from both event handling and scheduled scans.
.TP
.B system_exclusions
Glob patterns matched against the absolute path. Used to keep
ephemeral mounts like
.IR /proc ", " /sys ", and " /run
out of the baseline.
.SS [package_manager]
.TP
.B auto_rebaseline
When
.BR true ,
vigil refreshes the baseline for files touched by a package
transaction announced through the apt/dnf maintenance hooks.
.TP
.B backend
.B auto ", " apt ", " dnf ", or " none .
.SS [hooks]
.TP
.B signal_socket
Optional Unix\-domain socket on which third\-party tooling may signal
.B maintenance enter
and
.B maintenance exit
without invoking the CLI. Empty string disables.
.SS [security]
.TP
.B hmac_signing
When
.BR true ,
the audit log uses an HMAC\-chained record format. See
.BR vigil\-audit (7)
if installed, or
.I /usr/share/doc/vigil-baseline/AUDIT_HMAC_FORMAT.md .
.TP
.B hmac_key_path
Path to the HMAC key file. Must be mode 0600, owned by the
.B vigil
user.
.TP
.B verify_config_integrity
When
.BR true ,
.BR vigild (8)
computes a digest of this file at startup and refuses to start if the
on\-disk contents change without an operator acknowledgement.
.SS [detection]
.TP
.B disambiguate_on_detection
When
.BR true ,
content mismatches are additionally classified as
.BR page_cache_only ", " disk_modification ", " active_modification ", or " inconclusive
and the result is stored in the audit log's
.B disambiguation
column. The classification evicts the affected file's page cache via
.BR posix_fadvise (2)
with
.BR POSIX_FADV_DONTNEED ;
this is correct behaviour for incident triage but may be surprising as
steady\-state. Off by default.
.SS [database]
.TP
.B wal_mode
SQLite WAL journal mode. Recommended; the default.
.TP
.B audit_rotation_size
Bytes. The audit table is rotated to a compressed history file when it
exceeds this size.
.TP
.B audit_retention_days
Days of rotated audit history retained on disk before pruning.
.SS [watch.<group>]
One or more tables describing groups of paths to monitor. The group
name is opaque to vigil but is recorded in audit records and rendered
by
.BR vigil\-status (1).
.TP
.B severity
.B info ", " low ", " medium ", " high ", or " critical .
Drives alert routing and the colour of CLI output.
.TP
.B paths
Array of strings. Each entry may be a file, a directory (recursive),
or a path ending in
.B /
to denote a directory tree.
.SH FILES
.TP
.I /etc/vigil/vigil.toml
Default configuration path.
.TP
.I /usr/share/doc/vigil-baseline/vigil.toml.example
Annotated reference shipped by the package.
.TP
.I /etc/vigil/hmac.key
HMAC key file referenced by
.BR [security].hmac_key_path .
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR vigil (1),
.BR vigild (8),
.BR vigil\-config (1),
.BR systemd.service (5)
.SH NOTES
This file is parsed before privileges are dropped. A syntactically
invalid file causes
.BR vigild (8)
to exit before forking; the operator is expected to validate with
.B vigil config check
before restarting the service.
